<h1 id="select-page-layouts">Select page layouts</h1>


<p>This topic explains how to create and select page layouts in Microsoft Dynamics 365 Commerce.</p>
<h2 id="create-layouts-for-an-existing-page">Create layouts for an existing page</h2>
<div class="NOTE">
<h5>Note</h5>
<p>You can create layouts for an existing page only if that page has at least two modules under the main slot.</p>
</div>
<p>To create layouts for an existing page, follow these steps.</p>
<ol>
<li>Go to <strong>Pages</strong>, and find the existing page in the list. Use the search feature as you require.</li>
<li>Select the page, select <strong>Edit</strong> to check it out, and then select the page name to open it. Make a note of the module order.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Save as New Layout</strong>.</li>
<li>Enter a name for the layout, and then select <strong>OK</strong>.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Convert to Embedded Layout</strong>.</li>
<li>Change the order of the modules as you require, and make a note of the new order.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Save as New Layout</strong>.</li>
<li>Enter a name for the layout, and then select <strong>OK</strong>.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Change Layout</strong>, select the first layout that you created, and then select <strong>OK</strong>. Make a note of the module order. Change it so that it matches the module order that was saved with the layout.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Finish editing</strong> to check in the page, and then select <strong>Publish</strong> to publish it.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="select-a-different-layout-for-an-existing-page">Select a different layout for an existing page</h2>
<div class="NOTE">
<h5>Note</h5>
<p>You can select a different layout for an existing page only if the template that was used to create that page has more than one layout.</p>
</div>
<p>To select a different layout for an existing page, follow these steps.</p>
<ol>
<li>Go to <strong>Pages</strong>, and find the existing page in the list. Use the search feature as you require.</li>
<li>Select the page, select <strong>Edit</strong> to check it out, and then select the page name to open it.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Change layout</strong>.</li>
<li>Select the new layout for the page, and then select <strong>OK</strong>. The page editor is refreshed to show the new layout.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Finish editing</strong> to check in the page, and then select <strong>Publish</strong> to publish it.</li>
</ol>
